(4509,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=g9bIqKIdx80C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','The Convention deals with the obligation of each Contracting State to take adequate measures to prevent the unauthorized distribution on or from its territory of any programme-carrying signal transmitted by satellite.'),
(4510,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=WlN5DRysbxsC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','According to the Agreement, all goods bearing a false or deceptive indication of source, by which one of the Contracting States, or a place situated therein, is directly or indirectly indicated as being the country or place of origin, must be seized on importation, or such importation must be prohibited, or other actions and sanctions must be applied in connection with such importation.'),
(4511,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NkLzVwKdBGMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','The Locarno Agreement establishes a classification for industrial designs (the Locarno Classification). The competent offices of the Contracting States must indicate in official documents reflecting the deposit or registration of industrial designs the numbers of the classes and subclasses of the Classification to which the goods incorporating the designs belong. This must also be done in any publication the offices issue in respect of the deposit or registration of industrial designs.'),
