(5139,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=tjVnMwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','The latest edition of this popular casebook includes full coverage of the principles surrounding trademark acquisiton and registration under federal law, as well as infringement and dilution issues. Novel issues involving trademark usage in the on-line context are treated in depth. The book also deals with competitor false advertsing remedies under the Lanham Act and public enforcement of prohibitions against unfair and deceptive practices by the Federal Trade Commission. Case selection has been made with an eye towards holding student interest and provocative notes and questions make the book highly teachable.'),
